The paper proposes a new computing paradigm called Memcomputing, which is based on digital machines represented by electrical circuits with memory. The paper specifically applies this paradigm to solve Integer Linear Programming (ILP) problems, which is a well-known optimization problem in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which deals with new computing paradigms and technologies. 

The paper also discusses algorithms and optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). 

Finally, the paper uses simulations to compare the performance of their approach against a commercial solver, which is relevant to sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
